CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 6, 1945, pg. 8, reads: "Popular Couple United - Charming Nora Elizabeth Lee, daughter of Mr. and Mrs. William Lee of Homewood, and Julius Banks of Baltimore, were married Saturday, Sept. 29, in a quiet ceremony in Parish House of Corpus Christi Church, Homewood. Many out-of-town guests attended the nuptials.  Left to right: Charles Johnson of Boston, Mass.; Tommy Roberts, best man, Washington, D.C.; the groom and bride, Jerry Washington, maid of honor; Cleveland, Ohio, and Eva Ruth Greenlee, bridesmaid, of Pittsburgh. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Full length group portrait of Lee-Banks wedding party, from left: Charles Johnson, best man Tommy Roberts, groom Julius Banks, bride Nora Elizabeth Lee, maid of honor Jerry Washington, and Eva Ruth Greenlee, standing in front of fireplace with crucifix, another version
